      "source": {
        "value": "Pathfinder Bestiary",
        "author": ""
      },
      "creatureType": "Spirit",
      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p>The ghost commoner is an ordinary person who believes they died unjustly, usually due to foul play or betrayal.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>When some mortals die through tragic circumstances or without closure, they can linger on in the world. These anguished souls haunt a locale significant to them in life, constantly trying to right their perceived wrong or wrongdoings.</p><hr /><h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role (A88–A89):</strong> the king's tiefling stepbrother — Ileosa's poison-tool and first victim, walled up alive behind his own card-room (his bones lie at <strong>A11</strong>). <strong>The castle's kindest ghost and best informant:</strong> at A89 he can barely manifest (a misty horned old man rising from a harrow deck) until his bones are recovered — Zellara senses where they lie. Restored, he testifies that <strong>Ileosa poisoned King Eodred II</strong> (and that he shares the guilt), names her ritual — the <strong>Everdawn Pool</strong> in the <strong>Sunken Queen</strong>, fed by the lifeblood of thousands — and points the PCs to Domina's study (<strong>A90</strong>). See the A89 entry for his and Zellara's farewell gift.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
